-- ── easyappointments ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Easy!Appointments is a free, open-source, self-hosted online booking system that lets service businesses accept appointments through a customizable web widget.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Free / Open Source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Open-source project maintained by a core developer and community contributors$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$Greek$q$, $q$Hungarian$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Japanese$q$, $q$Dutch$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$Chinese (Simplified)$q$, $q$Polish$q$, $q$Danish$q$, $q$Russian$q$, $q$Turkish$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Easy!Appointments Review 2026: Features & Pricing$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Easy!Appointments is a free, open-source, self-hosted appointment booking system. See its features, setup requirements, pricing, and top alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Easy!Appointments (distributed under the project name easyappointments) is a free, open-source, self-hosted web application for scheduling and managing appointments. Unlike most scheduling tools on the market, it is not sold as a subscription SaaS product; instead, businesses download the source code and run it on their own server. The codebase is released under the GPL-3.0 license, with accompanying documentation under CC BY 3.0, meaning anyone can install, modify, and use it for personal or commercial purposes without licensing fees or per-booking commissions. The project traces its origins to developer Alex Tselegidis, with copyright notices in the source dating back to 2013. Since then it has grown into one of the most widely used open-source scheduling systems on GitHub, surpassing 3,000 stars and drawing an active global community that maintains translations, plugins, and platform integrations.

At its core, Easy!Appointments provides a public-facing booking page that a business can embed on its own website or share as a standalone link. Customers use it to choose a service, a specific provider or staff member, and an available appointment time, all without needing to create an account or place a phone call. Behind that public page sits an administrative dashboard where staff manage customers, services, providers, working hours, and booking rules such as buffer periods between appointments and how far in advance a customer may book. The system synchronizes two-way with Google Calendar so a provider's personal calendar always reflects new bookings and cancellations, and it supports virtual consultations through built-in Jitsi and Google Meet video links attached directly to confirmed appointments.

Technically, Easy!Appointments is a PHP application built on the CodeIgniter framework, requiring a standard web stack of Apache or Nginx, PHP, and a MySQL or MariaDB database. It can be installed manually by uploading the source files to a server, or deployed quickly using the official Docker image maintained by the project, which is also available as a one-click template on hosting platforms such as Railway. The software exposes a documented REST API and ships with official integration packages for WordPress, Joomla, and Drupal, plus a multi-lingual SDK that developers can use to build custom booking flows on top of the core engine. Beyond calendar sync, it includes SMS and email notification workflows for confirmations, reminders and cancellations, optional payment collection at the time of booking, and administrative reporting on booking volume across providers and services.

Because the software itself is free, there is no tiered SaaS pricing to speak of: any organization can run an unlimited number of providers, services, staff accounts, and appointments without seat limits or transaction fees. The real cost is self-hosting — a web server, a database, and optionally a domain and SSL certificate, which typically runs a few dollars a month through any standard hosting provider. For organizations that would rather not manage a server themselves, the maintainer and community offer optional paid services on a custom-quote basis, including managed hosting, white-labeling, bespoke feature development, migration from other booking systems, and dedicated support contracts.

Easy!Appointments is aimed at small and medium-sized service businesses — hair salons, medical and dental practices, consultants, tutors, fitness studios, spas, and similar appointment-driven operations — as well as developers, agencies, and IT teams who want full ownership of their scheduling data rather than being locked into a proprietary vendor platform. Reported users of the software include Doctors Without Borders, Neom, and Dolce & Gabbana, illustrating that it scales from a single freelancer's booking page up to larger organizational deployments. Because all data lives on infrastructure the business controls, the tool is particularly attractive to organizations with strict data-residency or privacy requirements — for example, clinics that would rather not store patient scheduling data with a third-party SaaS provider.

The interface has been translated by community contributors into more than twenty languages, including English, German, Greek, Hungarian, Portuguese, Spanish, Italian, Japanese, Dutch, French, Simplified Chinese, Polish, Danish, Russian, and Turkish, with the booking widget automatically detecting a visitor's browser language where a translation exists.

In the competitive landscape, Easy!Appointments sits opposite hosted commercial scheduling products such as Calendly, Acuity Scheduling, SimplyBook.me, and Setmore. Those tools offer a polished, zero-maintenance experience with built-in payment processing and marketing add-ons, typically billed per user per month. Easy!Appointments trades that convenience for control: no recurring subscription, no vendor lock-in, and full access to modify the codebase, at the cost of taking on hosting, security patching, backups, and upgrades in-house. For organizations already comfortable running their own servers, or that simply want to avoid a recurring per-seat bill, Easy!Appointments remains one of the most mature and actively maintained open-source alternatives to paid appointment-booking software.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '1c4c7eb8-4d91-4764-a260-79baa4f12ad4';

