-- ── écentic ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$écentic is an AI ecommerce optimization platform that simulates how AI shopping agents like ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity evaluate products, then rewrites listings to win more of those agent-driven purchases.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(NULL, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$écentic Review 2026: AI Shopping Agent Optimization$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$écentic simulates how AI shopping agents rank your products versus competitors and auto-optimizes listings. See its features and pricing plans here.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$écentic (styled with an accented e, and marketed at ecentic.ai) is an AI ecommerce optimization platform built for a moment its own marketing materials describe as agent commerce: a growing share of purchases where an AI assistant such as ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, or Perplexity compares products and completes a purchase on a shopper's behalf, without the shopper ever visiting a merchant's website directly. The company's core premise is that traditional SEO and conversion-rate optimization do not address this new buying channel, because the customer being persuaded is no longer a human scrolling a page but a language model comparing structured product data, so merchants need a different kind of optimization aimed specifically at how AI models parse and rank product listings.

The platform works by connecting to a merchant's existing catalog, primarily through native Shopify integration (écentic is listed on the Shopify App Store) with WooCommerce also supported, and then running each product simultaneously through multiple large language models, including GPT-4, Claude, Gemini, and Perplexity, to observe how each one ranks that product against category competitors. This simulation identifies attribute gaps, pricing or trust-signal weaknesses, and other reasons a product loses to a competitor in an agent's recommendation, broken down model by model so a merchant can see, for example, that a product performs well when evaluated by Gemini but poorly when evaluated by Claude. Based on that diagnosis, écentic can automatically rewrite product titles, descriptions, and structured data fields to improve how favorably an AI agent is likely to compare that listing against alternatives, effectively functioning as a continuous optimization loop rather than a one-time audit.

Beyond the core simulation and rewriting engine, écentic provides supplementary tools aimed at the broader agent-commerce ecosystem, including a UCP Playground for testing how a product behaves under the emerging Universal Commerce Protocol, a UCP validator for checking listing compliance with that protocol, and a documented MCP (Model Context Protocol) API that lets external systems query écentic's agent-visibility data programmatically. This API-first approach signals that écentic is building not just a merchant-facing dashboard but also infrastructure meant to plug into the broader stack of AI agents and commerce protocols as that ecosystem matures.

On pricing, écentic follows a freemium structure anchored by a Free Scan, a no-cost audit that gives a merchant a baseline read on their current win rate against AI shopping agents before they commit to a paid plan. Above that sits a mid-tier Compete plan (pricing not publicly disclosed at the time of research) and a Dominate plan priced at $449 per month, which includes continuous simulations across all supported AI models, automated content optimization, and Universal Commerce Protocol support. An Enterprise tier is available for larger catalogs and organizations with custom requirements, priced through direct sales conversations. écentic also runs partner programs offering extended access and discounted pricing, including deals for companies backed by Y Combinator and Techstars, and has announced at least one bundled offering combining its AI-visibility tooling with a compliance product from a partner called EU Presence.

écentic's target users are ecommerce merchants and brand teams, particularly those running Shopify or WooCommerce stores, who are trying to understand and improve their visibility inside AI-mediated shopping journeys as more consumers delegate research and purchasing decisions to AI assistants. This includes direct-to-consumer brands competing in crowded product categories where being the AI's top recommendation increasingly matters as much as ranking well in traditional search results, as well as agencies and consultants managing AI-visibility strategy across multiple merchant clients.

As a company, écentic is a relatively young entrant in the emerging category sometimes called answer engine optimization or AI shopping visibility, applied specifically to ecommerce catalogs rather than general content or brand mentions. Publicly available information does not confirm an exact founding year, headquarters location, or funding details, which is typical for an early-stage company still building out its public profile; its Crunchbase listing exists but does not surface these specifics in publicly available search results. Within this category, écentic sits alongside a broader wave of tools addressing AI visibility for brands and content generally, but differentiates itself by focusing specifically on structured product-catalog optimization for agent-driven shopping decisions, multi-model simulation rather than single-model testing, and direct integration with ecommerce platforms rather than requiring merchants to manually feed product data into a general-purpose AI-visibility tool.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '51409ee6-9c94-4bbc-977d-bb6ef59e11c5';

