-- ── Ech0 ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Ech0 is a free, open-source, self-hosted microblogging platform for publishing and sharing short personal posts, links, and media, with optional AI-powered digest and chat features.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Free / Open Source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(NULL, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Independent open-source project led by a single developer with community contributors$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Chinese$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Ech0 Review 2026: Self-Hosted Microblog Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Ech0 is a free, open-source, self-hosted microblog for sharing posts and links. See its features, deployment options, and AI capabilities.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Ech0 is a free, open-source, self-hosted publishing platform designed for individuals who want a personal microblog or timeline they fully own and control, rather than relying on a centralized social network. It is developed by a programmer using the handle lin-snow (also known as L1nSn0w), whose main repository, hosted at github.com/lin-snow/Ech0, describes the project as a new-generation, ultra-lightweight platform for personal idea sharing that supports the ActivityPub protocol, allowing an Ech0 instance to federate and interact with the broader Fediverse rather than existing as an isolated silo. The project positions itself against mainstream social platforms by emphasizing that a self-hosted Ech0 instance carries no advertising, no tracking, no subscription fee, and no risk of a third-party service shutting down or locking out an account holder.

Functionally, Ech0 gives a user a Markdown-based editor with live preview for composing short-form posts, thoughts, and links, along with tag management for organizing content and an RSS feed export so followers can subscribe outside of the platform itself. It supports rich media embedding, including images, audio, and video, and has built-in embed parsing for popular video platforms such as YouTube and Bilibili, the latter reflecting the project's roots in a primarily Chinese-speaking open-source developer community (the project maintains both an English and a Chinese README, and its support community is organized partly around a QQ group). A built-in comment system with moderation controls, along with like and sharing functionality, gives Ech0 some lightweight social interaction without turning it into a full social network with algorithmic feeds or advertising.

On the technical side, Ech0 is built primarily in Go for its backend, using an internally described Busen Data Bus architecture to keep components decoupled, paired with a web frontend built with modern JavaScript tooling. It is designed to be resource-efficient, explicitly targeting deployment on everything from a personal cloud server down to ARM single-board computers such as the Raspberry Pi, and ships as a compact container image. Deployment options include a single-command Docker or Docker Compose setup that the project claims can bring an instance online in under sixty seconds, a script-based installer, Kubernetes deployment via Helm charts for larger or clustered setups, and direct binary execution for users who prefer not to use containers at all. Authentication supports OAuth2 and OpenID Connect (OIDC) for integrating with existing identity providers, as well as passwordless login through Passkeys and WebAuthn.

Ech0's more advanced feature set extends into developer and AI tooling not commonly found in similarly small self-hosted projects: it exposes an open API and webhook system for integrating with external services, ships a command-line interface for automating administrative tasks, includes a real-time system log console and a terminal UI for server management, and — notably — integrates a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server, letting AI assistants and agents interact with an Ech0 instance's content programmatically. Built on top of that MCP integration are AI-powered features including automatically generated Recap digests summarizing recent posts, and a retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) based chat feature that lets a user or visitor converse with the content of their own timeline.

Ech0 is released under the AGPL-3.0-or-later license, which requires that any modified, publicly-served version of the software also make its source code available, a common choice for self-hosted server software intended to remain permanently open. The project's documentation notes that a separate commercial license is available for organizations that want to embed Ech0 in a proprietary product without the AGPL's source-disclosure requirements, though pricing for that arrangement is not published and would need to be negotiated directly with the maintainer. There is no official hosted or managed cloud version at the time of research; every Ech0 instance is run by the person or organization who deploys it, and community-run reference deployments exist primarily as demos or personal instances rather than as a commercial multi-tenant service.

As a niche, single-maintainer project, Ech0 is best compared to other small self-hosted microblogging and personal-publishing tools such as Plausible-adjacent Fediverse projects, Mataroa, or lightweight instances of Mastodon and WriteFreely, rather than to large venture-backed platforms. Its differentiators within that niche are its unusually broad feature set for a small project — ActivityPub federation, passkey authentication, an MCP server, and RAG-based AI chat over one's own posts — combined with a strong emphasis on minimal resource usage suitable for running on inexpensive hardware like a Raspberry Pi, which appeals to privacy-conscious hobbyists, developers, and self-hosting enthusiasts who want a lightweight alternative to running a full Mastodon server just to publish short personal updates.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '0bc21b7f-dfe2-4c44-a7ad-9cac54962d52';

